      • getBaseCommand

        public Object getBaseCommand()
        Gets the value of the 'baseCommand' field. Specifies the program to execute. If the value is an array, the first element is the program to execute, and subsequent elements are placed at the beginning of the command line in prior to any command line bindings. If the program includes a path separator character it must be an absolute path, otherwise it is an error. If the program does not include a path separator, search the `$PATH` variable in the runtime environment of the workflow runner find the absolute path of the executable.
        Returns:
        The value.
